data.name: addLogo.ToolTip
data.value:
Click to add a logo rule, rules can be defined to indicate what Network the episode was orginally aired in or what video and audio codecs the epsiode is encoded in etc...
A Logo package must be installed to display logos succesfully in Media Portal

data.name: checkBox_altImage.ToolTip
data.value: Enables the image loading routine as was used in older Versions. Try this if only if you find that images (such as banners) do not load or dissapear inside Mediaportal. May be slower under certain conditions and has no effect in the Configuration.

data.name: textBox_foromID.ToolTip
data.value: Your forom ID. When you register on this site, go to "rubriques" then to "votre compte", and copy/paste the string ID from the auto-identification URL provided there (starts after c= and stops before the last &)

data.name: textBox_TorrentDetailsRegex.ToolTip
data.value: Regular expression that is going to extract data from the details page of a specific torrent. The plugin is only looking for one group: <filecount> is the number of files in the torrent. Only torrents with one file will be taken into account

data.name: textBox_TorrentSearchRegex.ToolTip
data.value:
Regular expression that is going to extract data from the search results. Various group names are mandatory:
<name> is the name of the torrent file <link> is the url of the torrent file, used to download (should be relative to the search website address) <id> is the id of the torrent file, that is used to then go in the details and find out how many files there are in the release (the plugin filters out all multi part torrents; extracting files from a RAR is inpractical) <seeds> is the number of seeds for this torrents; this is used to sort the results from highest number to lowest <leechers> is the number of leechers; not displayed / used yet

data.name: comboBox_seasonFormat.ToolTip
data.value: Select the format to display the season listing in. Graphical will display the banners downloaded from online. Choose text if you dont want to display the downloaded banners but still have control over what is displayed

data.name: richTextBox_seasonFormat_Main.ToolTip
data.value:
Enter in the field(s) to be displayed in the main information pane of the season view. You can right click on this textbox to bring up a menu of available fields from the database.
Defaults to: <Series.Summary> e.g. The 4400 tells the stories of 4,400 abductees....
Use can enter '\n' to create newlines between fields
